label.value: TIMI Thrombus Grade - Coronary Thrombus TIMI Grade

value.value: Coronary Thrombus TIMI Grade (TIMI Thrombus Grade) A grade corresponding to thrombus development as defined in the grading system by the Thrombolysis in the Myocardial Infarction Group.

label.value: NHLBI CAD Grade - Coronary Artery Dissection NHLBI Grade

value.value: Coronary Artery Dissection NHLBI Grade (NHLBI CAD Grade) A grading system to describe coronary artery dissection per the NHLBI, American College of Cardiology, American Heart Association.

label.value: ARC STC Timing - Stent Thrombosis Coronary ARC Timing

value.value: Stent Thrombosis Coronary ARC Timing (ARC STC Timing) Categorization of the timing of coronary stent thrombosis occurrence per the classification schema described by the Academic Research Consortium.

label.value: ARC STC Grade - Stent Thrombosis Coronary ARC Grade

value.value: Stent Thrombosis Coronary ARC Grade (ARC STC Grade) A grading system to describe the coronary stent thrombosis per the classification schema described by the Academic Research Consortium.

label.value: Oral Diuretic Therapy Augmentation for Heart Failure

value.value: Initiation or intensification of oral diuretics to treat heart failure.

A phospholipid that is a component of the plasma membrane with signal transduction inducing activity. Phosphatidylinositol 4,5-bisphosphate (PIP2) is an intermediate that can be converted into either the second messenger signaling molecules, inositol 1,4,5-trisphosphate (IP3) and diacylglycerol (DAG), or phosphatidylinositol (3,4,5)-trisphosphate (PtdIns(3,4,5)P3; PIP3). Both PIP2 and PIP3 can act as docking phospholipids, which recruit signaling proteins to the plasma membrane and promotes the activation of several signaling cascades.

label.value: Weight Gain Due to Fluid Retention

value.value: A finding of rapid weight gain due to fluid retention.
An angiographic finding of pathologic material in a coronary vessel, which obstructs myocardial perfusion.
Any procedure that is undertaken to reestablish blood flow to the heart.
A reduction in the ability to perform or withstand activities that induce physical or mental exertion.
A finding of a hospitalization event due to a heart failure diagnosis.

label.value: Increase in B-type Natriuretic Peptide or N-terminal pro-B-type Natriuretic Peptide

value.value: A finding of an increased amount of either B-type natriuretic peptide or N-terminal pro-B-type natriuretic peptide
A finding of an increase in the jugular venous pressure, as measured by the height of the mean jugular venous waveform above the right atrium.
A finding of abnormal heart wall motion contractility in response to stress, and which is not seen at rest.

label.value: Intravenous Diuretic, Inotropic or Vasodilator Augmentation for Heart Failure

value.value: Initiation or intensification of intravenous diuretics, inotropics or vasodilators to treat heart failure.

label.value: Heart Failure by Invasive Diagnostic Technique

value.value: A finding of heart failure through an invasive diagnostic technique.
